Title: CONSTRUCTION OF CREASE-FREE FRACTALS USING DYADIC SPLINES  
Author: Mark A. Duchaineau 
Keyword: Key Words: Fractals, hierarchical splines, natural phenomena, geometry synthesis.  
Address: Davis  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science Computer Graphics Research Laboratory University of California,  
Abstract: A method for constructing crease-free fractals used for synthesizing landscapes, clouds, and mineral formations is presented. The method is simpler than previously known techniques because it is based on dyadic splines, a hierarchical spline representation introduced herein. The simplicity of the method lends itself to space- and time-efficient implementations and is flexible to use. 
